    <subsection>
        <title>Prompts</title>
        <p>
            Use the lecture videos to respond to the prompts below. Record each item in your prep work journal. 
            <ol>
                <li><p> Define the <alert>Wronskian</alert> of a set of functions. </p></li> 
                <li><p> When is a set of functions linearly independent? Write all definitions given in all videos. </p></li>
                <li><p> Describe the role of a <alert>trial function</alert> in the method of undetermined coefficients. </p></li>
                <li><p> Let for a function <m>f</m> be a function. What does an <alert>annhilator</alert> of <m>f</m> do? </p></li>
                <li><p> Write down the formula to compute variable parameters <m> \mu_i </m> in the method of variation of parameters. </p></li>
            </ol>
        </p>
